FG Development team...

Well, after a week long crash, I have my computer semi-operational 
again.  It is damaged and I have lost some of the material I was going 
to post to the list for consideration.

Here is what I am working on...

1)  Formal specs

I think we should seriously start specing out the various subsystems 
(kernel, database, aircraft models, ATC, etc).  One thing I really don't 
want to do is rewrite code.  The stronger our base foundation, the 
easier a time we will have in writing this.  We need to resolve baseline 
platform issues (screen resolutions, primitive graphics) above all else, 
in my opinion.  Things like what type of math for graphics math (fixed 
or floating point), memory and processor targets, issues unique to 
windowed OS's, and so on.  We need to start building some tools for our 
primitive data types and get some crude operational code together, even 
if it isn't portable, so we can see how things will fit. 

I'm getting a bad feeling about getting too deep into the low level 
stuff right now.  I think we should be working high level for the moment 
and take it downward when we start see how this program is going to fit 
together.

I have a reason for this view.  Eric has done some wonderful work.  (I 
have barely starting coding, I basically have a maximized window with 
the caption "Flight Gear").  I am really pushing the Bombardier 
connection and I would like something to materialize there.  If they 
want to see more, I would like to send them some working code so they 
have some visuals.  It will help show that we are working.

Just some thoughts on the issue.  I am currently drafting a detailed FG 
overview to give us a firmer framework to look at.  A copy is going to 
Bombardier, and I will post it here for review.  

2)  Bombardier

I spoke with Francine Blackburn at Bombardier Canada.  She was pleased 
to hear from me.  I have sent her all available info on FG, including 
excerpts from our mailing list and a letter detailing our goals and 
requirements, as well as request for any assistance.  If we can build 
relationships here, it will go a long way in helping us get off the 
ground, as it were.  :)

I will keep you posted.  (And if I go to Montreal, yes, I will take 
pictures.  :)

3)  Win32 prototype

I have a window, folks.  I am plowing through my graphics programming 
books and sticking together a system for generating views.  Expect to 
see the first inklings of the ODL here.  If I can get a cube on the 
screen from a scenery file, it will be a start.  I will co-ordinate with 
Eric on that so we can begin to get something going here.

The way I see things, Eric is working bottom up, I am working top down. 
 We'll meet in the middle somewhere.  :)

4)  General comments

Love your ideas, Curt.  Let's subdivide the world.  Build a simple 
database showing what regions cover what areas of Long/Lat, then we can 
forget about co-ordinate problems and do the world flat regions joined 
together.  I also want to hear ideas on weather here, for haze effects, 
etc.  (Do we want raindrops splattering on the windscreen?  I do.  :)

To the aero-modellers:  Think about how you want to "assemble" aircraft. 
 What kind of detail, flight handling characteristics, etc.  I would 
love a tool where we can design aircraft by dragging pieces together in 
3D and let the program work out the flight model, which we can then 
tweak.  :)

5)  Final comment

Yes, folks, I am quite excited about this project.  :)

Take care, one and all,

Matt
