Before I get into Matt's message, a status report.  I finally got around to 
adding some minimal palette support.  The first 16 colors in the palette
are going to be the "standard" 16 color VGA colors.  I also wrote two drivers
one to display random lines (10 per second) and one to display color bars.  
So far they work under OS/2 and DJGPP.  (Yes! real stuff on the screen) I'll be 
trying it out on X tonight and will put the modified code on my web site.  

