I'm having problems getting the code to port to compilers without a
64 bit integral type.  I think I'm going to "typedef FG_INT64 double;"
on those machines.  We'll lose some precision, but it should be OK.
As far as fixed versus fp, I think that should be a compile time
decision.  I've written a program "fp_test" to determine the fastest
way of doing various operations.  For the machines I've tried 
(Pentium, SPARC), integer is fastest for add and subtract, but 
float is fastest for multiply and divide.  So what's happening is I've defined 
macros in "fgfixed.h" for the various operations.  They are of the form
F_ADD(x,y), F_ADD64(x,y), F_SUB(x,y), etc.

