Greetings,

I thought I would just give a little status report of what I was
playing around with this weekend.

Let me start out by saying that I in no way wish to pre-empt anyone
who may also be working on similar things ... 

Anyways, I grabbed the flight model code out of the ACM program and
was able to compile a ".o" ... it is completely untested, so I don't
know exactly what I have going yet (if anything.)  Right now it is
just a simple ".o" and not a flight gear module ... I will look into
doing that next.  I will also have to look into issues such as what
sorts of units it expects, and how it assumes the world is being
modeled ... plenty to keep me busy.  :-)

ACM also comes with a lot of other flight sim code including a HUD, so
I might try to get some of that working at the same time.  It also
comes with a lot of multi-player, combat type code ... I am going to
look at preserving as much of that as I can.  There is no sense in
ripping it out if it is already there. 

My goal is to wire in the flight model and HUD so that you can
actually fly ... without scenery though ... it will look like you are
in 0 visibility conditions (if it works.)  :-)

The whole point of this exercise is to get as many things working as
possible with as little effort as possible.  But to do it in such a
way that the various modules can be replaced with modules that are
much better down the road as time permits.

Now if anyone out there is working on similar things, please don't
worry.  Flight Gear is a platform that should support many flight
models ... each with their own advantages/disadvantages.

I have a long way to go before I will have anything close to useful to
show, but I will be sure to let everyone know when/if I do.

Thanks,

Curt.
