> 1. What is an "acceptable frame rate"? 5,10,15 fps?

I'd say 10 fps is about a minimum.

> 2. What will be our initial targeted screen resolution?

All of the above.  The X and OS/2 versions (fgnew.zip) are currently 
pixel resolution independant (but not color depth independant).  At home 
I've had the DJGPP version working at 320x200x8, 640x480x8, 1024x768x8.
I assume it would also work at 1280x1024x8, but my monitor doesn't support
that resolution.

The device drivers should automatically size themselves on startup to
fit the bitmap they are given.  They should also resize themselves if
their *_init routine gets a FG_BITMAP_CHANGE message.

> 3. P-133 optimal or middle of the road?

We'll fing out when we get there.  I'm using a P-90 now, but who knows
what I'll be using at release.

> 4. what about other platforms (ie LINUX, Mac)? Are the same capabilities
> possible there?

So far there have been few problems.  (Although I haven't gotten to 24 bit
color, sound, mice, or any Mac stuff yet.)

Eric
